---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Bruce Web Development"
  description="About Bruce: a student web developer in Winnipeg building fast, modern websites for small businesses."
>
  <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 md:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">About me</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-lg leading-relaxed">
      I'm Bruce, a student developer based in Winnipeg. I build websites for
      small businesses using modern tools that make sites fast, secure, and
      cheap to run.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-prose leading-relaxed">
      Being a student means two things for you: my rates are lower than an
      agency's, and I care a lot about doing good work — every project goes
      in my portfolio. I'll always be straight with you about what I can do
      and how long it will take.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-8">
      <a href="/contact/" class="text-link">Let's talk about your project</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
